Issue Identification:
- Determine email platform (Outlook, OWA, Gmail, mobile)
- Identify specific issue (sending, receiving, syncing, access)
- Check if issue affects one mailbox or multiple users
- Note any error messages received

{% if issue_type == 'mailbox_full' %}
Mailbox Full Resolution:
- Check current mailbox size and quota
- Review Deleted Items and empty if needed
- Check Sent Items folder size
- Archive old emails if archiving is available
- Increase mailbox quota if approved
- Educate user on mailbox management
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'sync_issues' %}
Outlook Sync Issues:
- Verify Outlook is connected (check status bar)
- Check Send/Receive settings
- Repair Outlook profile
- Clear Outlook cache
- Recreate OST file if needed
- Test with Outlook Web Access to isolate issue
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'shared_mailbox' %}
Shared Mailbox Access:
- Verify user has permissions to shared mailbox
- Add Full Access and/or Send As permissions
- Auto-map shared mailbox or add manually
- Check if credentials need updating
- Verify licensing requirements are met
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'spam_filtering' %}
Spam/Filtering Issues:
- Check spam/junk folder for missing emails
- Review quarantine for blocked messages
- Whitelist sender domain if legitimate
- Adjust spam filter sensitivity if needed
- Report false positives/negatives to security team
{% endif %}

General Email Troubleshooting:
- Verify network connectivity
- Check email service status
- Test webmail access
- Verify account is not locked or disabled
- Check for Outlook updates

Resolution:
- Confirm email functionality is restored
- Document resolution steps
- Provide tips to prevent recurrence
- Escalate to Exchange/M365 admin if server-side issue
